<title>USA: BMC Software,other stocks favored-Barron's.</title>
<headline>BMC Software,other stocks favored-Barron's.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-07-06</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares of BMC Software Inc and other stocks were recommended by fund manager John LaPorte, Barron's reported.</p>
<p>LaPorte, who manages T. Rowe Price's $4.5 billion New Horizons fund, said BMC Software will benefit from a continuing emphasis on networked computer environments within the workplace.</p>
<p>The company's shares closed Thursday down 1/2, at 53-7/8.</p>
<p>LaPorte also recommended the following stocks:  </p>
<p>3Com Corp</p>
<p>Maxim Integrated Products Inc</p>
<p>Xilinx Inc</p>
<p>CoreStaff Inc</p>
<p>AccuStaff Inc</p>
<p>Watsco Inc</p>
<p>Henry Schein Inc</p>
<p>General Nutrition Companies Inc</p>
<p>Paychex Inc</p>
<p>Medic Computer System Inc</p>
<p>IDEXX Laboratories Inc</p>
